Description




 We currently have a vacancy for an
 **ETL Developer** 
 fluent in English, to offer his/her services as an expert who will be based in Stockholm, Sweden. The work will be carried out either in the company’s premises or on site at customer premises. In the context of the first assignment, the successful candidate will be integrated in the Development team of the company that will closely cooperate with a major client’s IT team on site.




**Your tasks** 




 Data modelling and data warehouse architecture;




 Design and develop new and optimize existing ETL flows for system integration, automated dataflows, data validation and storage;




 Contribute to the design of the overall solution architecture, interfaces, services, infrastructure configuration, security and access policies;




 Optimize performance of new and existing ETL flows;




 Testing ETL solutions and integration testing individually or in collaboration with other teams;




 FME flow management of workflows, job scheduling, resource allocation, error handling, monitoring, ensuring scalability.




**Requirements** 




 University degree in computer science (or equivalent) with minimum 3 years of experience in IT OR non university degree with minimum 6 years of experience in IT;




 At least 3 years of experience as ETL developer/Engineer developer using FME;




 At least 3 years of experience using SQL of which a minimum of 1 year using TransactSQL;




 Experience in FME flow management of workflows, job scheduling, resource allocation, error handling, monitoring,ensuring scalability;




 Experience in performance optimisation of ETL flows;




 Experience in data modelling and data warehouse architecture;




 Knowledge of the software development lifecycle in both: waterfall and Agile/DevOps modes;




 Experience working with work item management tool ( Azure DevOps);




 Experience producing and maintaining technical documentation;




 Experience of working in an Agile environment;




 Experience with DevOps practices, CI/CD and automation;




 Advanced TransactSQL skills and experience in SSIS;




 Excellent command of the English language.

For an international institution in Stockholm, Sweden, we are urgently looking for a Senior BI Analyst. The Senior BI Analyst is expected to perform the tasks related to the projects, products, applications and services developed in the DTS Digital Solutions section related to data warehouses and business intelligence.










 EU candidates are welcome to apply.
 **Candidates need to be based in Stockholm or willing to relocate to Stockholm.** 










 Candidates need to be fluent in English. A work permit is required, but not provided. This position is long-term and open for contractors.










**Tasks and Responsibilities:** 



* Perform business analysis for BI and other IT solutions;
* Product management of assigned product;
* Data warehouse design;
* Data modelling;
* Design ETL processes;
* Testing ETL and BI solutions individually or in collaboration with other teams;









**Profile:** 



* Bachelor or Master degree;
* +6 years of Business Analysis experience for BI and Data Warehouse solutions;
* Experience in Business Analysis for BI solutions
* Experience as Data warehouse designer;
* Experience in business process analysis using BPMN;
* Experience in requirements elicitation and Business Analysis using best practices (BABOK);
* Experience working with work item management tools (e.g. Azure DevOps, TFS or Jira);
* Experience producing and maintaining design documentation;
* Experience in product management;
* Experience in Sparx Enterprise Architect;
* Work experience in the area of public health is an advantage;
* Fluent in English;









**Interested:** 




 If you are interested in this opportunity, please forward your CV to resume@all-european-careers.com.










 Following countries are part of the European Union: Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Croatia, Republic of Cyprus, Czech Republic, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Ireland, Italy, Latvia, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain and Sweden.

**Company Description** 




 Priority Engineering Ltd is a multinational Mechanical, Electrical and Instrumentation Engineering contractor, established in 2017 to deliver excellent standards across these sectors. The company operates with core values of honesty, integrity, and collaborative working. We have live projects across Europe, and are currently investing in our team for current and upcoming projects in Sweden.










**Role Description** 




 This is a full-time hybrid role for a Graduate Electrical Engineer, located in Stockholm. Working directly under the Operations Manager, it is an opportunity to grow and learn all aspects of contracting in the field of engineering across multiple regions. The Engineer will be responsible for tasks related to Design, Engineering, Procurement and Construction. The primary language for the role will be English.










**Qualifications** 




 Relevant third level qualification in Electrical or Building Services Engineering essential; 




 Work experience in a contracting environment advantageous but not essential; 




 Ability to work both individually and as part of a multi-functional team;




 Excellent IT Skills essential;




 Excellent communication and organisation skills essential; 










**Salary and renumeration package will be in line with industry standards**
